cff-version: 1.2.0
title: >-
  ENFIELD: Formal Adversarial Testing of LLM-Generated Code
  for Industrial Robots
message: >-
  If you use this software, please cite it using the metadata
  from this file.
type: software
authors:
  - given-names: Yunus Emre
    family-names: Cogurcu
    email: yunusemrecogurcu@gmail.com
    affiliation: Çukurova University
    orcid: 'https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9229-9657'
  - given-names: Georgios
    family-names: Spathoulas
    affiliation: >-
      Norwegian University of Science and Technology (NTNU),
      Dept. of Information Security and Communication Technology
repository-code: 'https://github.com/dryuemco/industrial_robot_security'
url: 'https://www.enfield-project.eu/'
abstract: >-
  A formal adversarial testing framework for detecting safety
  violations (ISO 10218) in industrial robot code generated by
  Large Language Models. Includes a vendor-neutral Task IR format,
  AST-based watchdog with 8 attack type detectors (A1-A8), and
  runtime safety monitors for ROS2 Humble simulation environments.
  Simulation-only — no physical robot deployment.
keywords:
  - adversarial-testing
  - llm-safety
  - industrial-robots
  - iso-10218
  - ros2
  - ast-analysis
  - robot-security
license: Apache-2.0
version: 0.1.0
date-released: '2026-02-01'

